body: You forget to include `vendor` files, look at the files in `dist` directory, you ignore `How we can reproduce it`, so we can't provide which file you forgot to add
in dev mode I have `src_test_js.js` file
I recommend to use `HtmlWebpackPlugin` to avoid these errors in future
@alexander-akait But what about in production? There is no `src_test_js.js` file and the error still occurs

@alexander-akait Here's a repository that replicates the error. If webpack 5.18.0 is used, no error. 5.19.0 - error

https://github.com/davidmerrique/webpack-dependon-error

I can't understand what do you want from webpack here, you don't include extracted chunk, so code will not work

> If webpack 5.18.0 is used, no error. 5.19.0 - error

webpack fix some problems and better split chunks between entry points

Again you use `HtmlWebpackPlugin` to auto generate `script` or disable `deterministic` chunk names using https://webpack.js.org/configuration/optimization/#optimizationchunkids in production, just use `named`

> I'm not able to use HTMLWebpackPlugin in our codebase.

> disable deterministic chunk names using https://webpack.js.org/configuration/optimization/#optimizationchunkids in production, just use named

`home` depend on `app`, so `test.js` can be reused between `home` and `app`, so you have `src_test_js.js`, otherwise you will have duplicated code

It is not breaking change, it is fix, because it was not working as expected, what is why you should generate `html` file from stats or using a plugin for this. You can found it in docs https://webpack.js.org/guides/output-management/

@alexander-akait I included `HtmlWebpackPlugin` and I get the same error: https://github.com/davidmerrique/webpack-dependon-error/tree/html-webpack-plugin

It generates this:
```html
<script src="runtime.js"></script>
<script src="app.js"></script>
<script src="home.js"></script>
```

`Uncaught ReferenceError: __webpack_require__ is not defined`

When script tags are missing you won't get an error. It will just do nothing.

Here it seem to be a bug. Looks like a require requirement is missing...

issue.title: fix #12562

repository.name: webpack
repository.description: A bundler for javascript and friends. Packs many modules into a few bundled assets. Code Splitting allows for loading parts of the application on demand. Through "loaders", modules can be CommonJs, AMD, ES6 modules, CSS, Images, JSON, Coffeescript, LESS, ... and your custom stuff.
